I"v<p>If one looks at <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/affect-reflects-ideological-structures">affective states</a> as part of a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/phenomenal-space-is-adaptive">space</a> governed by a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/continuous-state-dynamical-systems-share-a-common-structure">dynamical system</a>, then <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/few-shot-learning-exapts-text-generation">language models</a> can be used to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/constraining-text-generation-to-existing-strings-enables-extraction">generate</a> well-calculated <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamical-systems-have-a-certain-anatomy">perturbations</a> for <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/attractors-and-repellors-have-opposite-behaviors-in-dynamical-systems">breaking out of spirals</a>.</p>
